            <entry xml:id="entry_īwzærdyg" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>īwzærdyg</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ewzærdug</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>преданный</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>faithful</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из %iīw-zærd-yg%i буквально „единосердечный“; ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>yakdil</w>
                        <gloss><q>единодушный</q></gloss></mentioned> (%iуаk%i ‘один’, %idil%i
                    ‘сердце’), <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>ertguli</w>
                        <gloss><q>преданный</q></gloss></mentioned> из %ierti%i ‘один’ и %iguli%i
                    ‘сердце’. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dyzærdyg"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It is from %iīw-zærd-yg%i, literally it means „of one heart“;
                    cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>yakdil</w>
                        <gloss><q>of one mind</q></gloss></mentioned> (%iуаk%i ‘one’, %idil%i
                    ‘heart’), <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>ertguli</w>
                        <gloss><q>faithful</q></gloss></mentioned> from %ierti%i ‘one’ and %iguli%i
                    ‘hearth’. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dyzærdyg"/>.</etym>
            </entry>
